    <name>
      <text>10.3.2 (Understanding Riemann sums (x^2 on [0,6]))</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Set the slider to \(n={@n@}\) - you should see that the left sum is {@ls@} and the right sum is {@rs@}.</p><p>Complete the following calculation which shows how the value of the {@LorR@} sum is obtained:</p><p>\(\displaystyle \sum_{i={@imin@}}^{@imax@} f\left({@i*Rend/n@}\right)\times\frac{{@Rend@}}{@n@}\)</p><p>\(\displaystyle = {@Rend/n@}\bigg({@(firstbit),simp=false@}+\)&nbsp;[[input:ans1]] \(+{@lastbit@}\bigg)\)</p><p>[[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The missing term is when \(i={@missingterm@}\) so the missing value is \(f({@missingterm@})={@ta1@}\).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
